title: For Trade:  AR Parts needed!
postcontent: Now all I need is a gas block, tube, barrel nut, fore grip and charging handle for a carbine barrel.  Used is fine... What do you got, and what do you want for it?I have some stuff for trade, and a little cash if the price is right.I just got another set of Spyderco bug knives like the one pictured, except they are all signed by Nutnfancy(YouTube gun/knife reviewer celeb) that I will trade for the right parts... I'll post pic when they get here. -.22lr ammo in a variety of brands etc(see picture)-9mm ammo. a couple hundred rounds or so a of factory reloads from tactical ammo.-Simmons Prairie Master 8-32X44 Rifle Scope.-Spyderco C133set new in box... you can still get the three knives seperatly for around $60 or so, but the set was discontinued last year making it instantly collectible and worth more than the individual knives.  You never see this set for sale anymore.  -Spyderco Delica 1 PE Thin Clip.  Used in excellent condition.  This is the earliest version of the Gen 1 with G2 steel, and the thin plastic molded clip... circa 1990.later on they went to a thicker clip and AUS8a steel.  I tied a Sebenza style paracord lanyard on it because I don't use the clip for fear of bending or breaking it.-Spyderco "LBK" very rare very collectible due to the packaging it comes in.  They are supposed to be called LadyBugs, but in early 90's when they started selling knives to the millitary they initially made a limited number of these because the sales manager at the time thought the troops wouldn't like a knife called the "ladybug" so the called it a LBK (acronym for little big knife) I have talked to everybody from hardcore Spyderco experts/collectors to the lady that has been in charge of Spyderco customer service since the company began, and nobody has seen one of these before.  I got the information I have from Sal Glesser(Spyderco's founder and the designer of the knife) via the Spyderco forum.   Spyderco, and it's fans now refer to all their small knives like the ladybug, man bug, jester, dragonfly etc, as LBK's or "little big knives" because they are able to get big knife performance in a little package.  These knives are where it all started, making them a cool piece of Spyderco's history. I have 3 of these.  I am keeping at least one for myself, and will only sell/trade the other 2 to someone that appreciates them and their significance as much as I do... or I would have put them up on eBay a long time ago. Please don't make any lowball offers on these.  I can't be sure of their value because none have been sold before to compare it to, but I have a general idea of what I want for them. I have one up for auction on eBay starting at $100

title: For Sale:  Kel-Tec PLR-16 .223 Handgun (5% discount for LTC holders)
postcontent:
Selling a lightly-used Kel-Tec PLR-16 .223/5.56 NATO pistol that I purchased new approximately 3 years ago.  It's in good shape and has only been on the firing line a few times.  It's a lot of power in a small package and is a powerful defensive tool to have in your home, car or boat.  Comes with 3 x 30 round metal magazines. Add ons:Kel-Tec Compact Forend with integrated picatinny rail on the bottomKel-Tec Muzzle Break KitManufacturer's Description:Calibers: 5.56mm NATOWeight unloaded: 3.4lbs 1.55kgLength: 18.5" 467mmBarrel length: 9.2" 234mmTwist: 1:7" 1.229mmCapacity: AR15 compatible magazineTrigger pull: 5.5-7.5lbs 24.4-33.4NSight radius: 12.5" 318mmMuzzle velocity: 2600fps
 
The PLR-16 is a gas operated, semi-automatic pistol chambered in 5.56 mm NATO caliber. It is intended to be the ideal silhouette shooting and hunting pistol. The rifling is 1 turn in 7 inches, right hand twist. The PLR-16 has a conventional, long-stroke gas-piston operation and utilizes the proven Johnson/Stoner breech locking system. The rear sight is adjustable for windage. The front sight is similar to an AR-15 style rifle, and adjustable for elevation. An integrated MIL-STD-1913 Picatinny rail will accept a multitude of standard accessories. The muzzle is threaded 1/2-28 TPI to accept standard attachments such as a muzzle brake or flash hider. Except for the barrel, bolt, sights, and mechanism, the PLR-16 pistol is made entirely of high-impact glass fiber reinforced polymer.The accessories available for the PLR-16 include forend with Picatinny rail on the bottom, scope rings, dynamic deflecting operating handle, single point sling, and a muzzle brake specifically design for the 9.2" barrel of the PLR-16.
5% discount on listed price for any buyer with a valid Texas License To Carry (LTC) permit.  Please be prepared for me to take a photograph of your LTC and driver's license as part of my records of the sale.  Any buyer without a Texas License To Carry (LTC) must transfer this weapon through an FFL dealer.Important note: I reserve the right to refuse to sell to any person for any reason or no reason at all.  Any bill of sale will include sections where you must affirm that you are legally able to purchase and possess this firearm in the state of Texas.
